The paper deals with parameterized complexity and graph algorithms, which are typically found in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of tree-width and clique-width also suggests a possible fit in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions Set Cover and Directed Hamiltonicity, which are problems in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), respectively.
